The paper discusses the accessibility and long term availability of raw experimental data in experimental fracture mechanics. This topic is related to several sub-categories in computer science, including computer engineering (cs.CE) for developing systems to manage and store data, cryptography and security (cs.CR) for ensuring the privacy and security of data, digital libraries (cs.DL) for providing access to data, databases (cs.DB) for managing and querying data, and software engineering (cs.SE) for developing tools and processes to ensure reproducibility.
